                    },
                    "feminized_mentor": {
                      "value": false
                    }
                  }
                },
                {
                  "uid": "d14d38be-5add-553d-9e69-7523ebf853f2",
                  "componentName": "SimpleText",
                  "dataSource": "{82B5FC37-098F-5B32-9EEB-E5C618D3105D}",
                  "params": {},
                  "fields": {
                    "noMargin": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "borderTop": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "isBold": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "lettrine": {
                      "value": true
                    },
                    "title": {
                      "value": "Overloaded schedules"
                    },
                    "titleColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "text": {
                      "value": "Many of the meetings between mentor and protégé took place in cities where Sir Colin was conducting. Caballé Domenech would attend Sir Colin’s rehearsals and concerts and sit in on Sir Colin’s master classes. But Caballé Domenech had his own career to cultivate, appearing in cities from Stockholm to Pamplona and Odense to Barcelona. The question then was how to develop their relationship?"
                    },
                    "textColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "usText": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "blackText": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "blackBackground": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "removeLine": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "backgroundColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    }
                  }
                },
                {
                  "uid": "2c58896c-fcbf-59a0-82fc-9db53928db37",
                  "componentName": "SimpleText",
                  "dataSource": "{6FCBBBF2-AC31-5CBD-AFF3-813F8F59CA30}",
                  "params": {},
                  "fields": {
                    "noMargin": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "borderTop": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "isBold": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "lettrine": {
                      "value": true
                    },
                    "title": {
                      "value": "Reading List"
                    },
                    "titleColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "text": {
                      "value": "Sir Colin&rsquo;s ingenious solution for initiating a dialogue was to urge Caballé Domenech in the direction of literature. To begin with, he provided volumes from his own library, beginning with Friedrich Schiller's <i>Don Carlos</i>. Next, Sir Colin thought of <i>Die Rauber</i> (<i>The Highwayman</i>), a wild melodrama of Schiller's youth, and a cardinal document of the movement known as <i>Sturm und Drang</i>."
                    },
                    "textColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "usText": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "blackText": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "blackBackground": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "removeLine": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "backgroundColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    }
                  }
                },
                {
