                {
                  "uid": "571eb9a0-12dd-51eb-8d4d-ddae7d6399b1",
                  "componentName": "SimpleText",
                  "dataSource": "{302DCC75-EF5C-546D-B358-A836AA120769}",
                  "params": {},
                  "fields": {
                    "noMargin": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "borderTop": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "isBold": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "lettrine": {
                      "value": true
                    },
                    "title": {
                      "value": "Unexpected lessons"
                    },
                    "titleColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "text": {
                      "value": "Ultimately perhaps what will most impact Caballé Domenech in the years to come will be the sense of ease and the playfulness he witnessed in his time with Sir Colin. “All the things conductors think they should do, they have to unlearn. Maybe what I have to offer is this sort of unlearning, urging Josep to look between the bar lines, to consider the whole flexibility of music, all the different things you can make it mean.”"
                    },
                    "textColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "usText": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "blackText": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "blackBackground": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "removeLine": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "backgroundColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    }
                  }
                },
                {
                  "uid": "4ec39f66-35ee-504f-8613-1a03614cdccb",
                  "componentName": "SimpleText",
                  "dataSource": "{2A1BF63E-2AFE-5C28-AB99-6591CEC31A60}",
                  "params": {},
                  "fields": {
                    "noMargin": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "borderTop": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "isBold": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "lettrine": {
                      "value": true
                    },
                    "title": {
                      "value": "Professional Impact"
                    },
                    "titleColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "text": {
                      "value": "A young conductor who is already sparking excitement, Caballé Domenech aroused particularly keen interest during his concerts in Madrid in April and May 2003, when he conducted both the Spanish National Orchestra and the Spanish National Radio Orchestra."
                    },
                    "textColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "usText": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "blackText": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "blackBackground": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "removeLine": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "backgroundColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    }
                  }
                },
                {
                  "uid": "cf7bf5d5-f7c3-5bed-912a-bc4f3ed4b171",
                  "componentName": "SimpleText",
                  "dataSource": "{674C697C-167A-5956-B9AF-E7764580074E}",
                  "params": {},
                  "fields": {
                    "noMargin": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "borderTop": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "isBold": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "lettrine": {
                      "value": true
                    },
                    "title": {
                      "value": "Personal Impact"
                    },
                    "titleColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "text": {
                      "value": "“The most important thing I learned from Sir Colin, really, was his attitude,” Caballé Domenech says, “his relaxed way of approaching and solving artistic problems – and human problems, as well, which he feels are the same thing. He has great trust in people.”"
                    },
                    "textColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "usText": {
                      "value": ""
